to Emmaus</strong></h3><p>Life is less about sprinting toward healing and more like that long walk to Emmaus. Remember how the disciples trudged along, hearts heavy, eyes blinded by grief? They didn't recognize Him at first. But He was there—listening, explaining, reframing their pain, walking every dusty step.</p><p>That's the rhythm of our healing. Jesus doesn't stand at the finish line waiting for us to arrive. He walks the road with us. He unveils Hi…</p>"}